    {
      "id": "9272cdfdab72183b45db15fee6fafaff33009776",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2025-07-01 02:29:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> I've disabled the rocky9.5 builds on lustre-reviews now.  They were just enabled on Friday, but I'm not sure why they aren't working.\n\nNo, this fails further down - https://git.whamcloud.com/?p=fs/lustre-release.git;f=contrib/lbuild/funcs.sh;hb=refs/changes/93/59993/1#l202.\n\nIt wants rhel-9.5, but sees rhel9.5. Funny, enough autodetect_distro() correctly returns rhel-9.5. But, we explicitly remove the dash:\n\n    if [ -z \"$DISTRO\" ] ; then\n        DISTRO=$(autodetect_distro)\n        # remove separator\n        DISTRO=${DISTRO/-/}\n    fi\n    DISTROMAJ=${DISTRO%%.*}\n\nThis causes the failure in autodetect_target().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
